News24 CorrespondentJohannesburg Metro Police. (File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; A Johannesburg metro cop is in critical condition after being hit by a taxi during a stop and search operation in Orange Farm, the Johannesburg Metro Police Department said on Friday."She has sustained fractures to her left arm, left leg, pelvis as well as her ribs," spokesperson Chief Superintendent Wayne Minnaar said in a statement."The taxi driver was charged at the Orange Farm police station for reckless and negligent driving."Officer Beverly Kruger, 46, remains in Milpark Hospital following the incident on Thursday morning.She was hit while working on Welgefonden Road. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.